sentence: U.S. stock futures were slightly higher on Thursday, after stocks on Wednesday briefly hit new records, and as the market awaited data on jobless claims and consumer prices.
In economic data out Thursday, initial jobless claims for the week ended Feb. 21, out at 8:30 a.m. E.T.
are expected to have risen to 290,000 from 283,000 in the prior week, with the consensus range between 279,000 to 300,000, according to data compiled by Econoday.
Out at the same time, the consumer price index for January is seen slipping 0.6% compared to a 0.4% drop in December.
The consensus range is between a decline of 0.8% and a decline of 0.2%.
The durable goods orders is meanwhile seen gaining 2.0% in January compared to a 3.4% drop in December.
The consensus range for January is for a 2.1% drop to a 4.0% gain.
Later this morning, at 9:00 a.m., the Federal Housing Finance Agency's house price index is seen gaining 0.5% in December compared to a 0.8% gain in November.
The consensus range is between a 0.4% gain and a 1.0% gain.
In equities, software provider Salesforce.com ( CRM ) shares jumped 12.6% after reporting as-expected Q4 results Q1 revenue guidance and as it raised its revenue guidance range for fiscal 2016.
